08/12/2002
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia and Albania reportedly will sign a protocol on 15 December starting joint border patrols by the end of 2004. According to Macedonian A1 TV, Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and his Albanian counterpart Pandeli Majko will meet in Skopje to seal the agreement. The initiative, organised under the auspices of NATO, would authorise establishment of a co-ordinating body that would include representatives of all ministries related to border control. NATO Director for the Balkans Robert Serry welcomed the general improved relations. (A1 TV, BBC - 06/12/02)
